The paper deals with reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) that focuses on training agents to make decisions based on rewards. The paper also deals with robotics (cs.RO), as it tests the proposed method on robotic environments. The use of a Q-filter and auxiliary behaviour cloning loss suggests a focus on deep reinforcement learning (cs.AI), and the use of OpenAI Gym suggests a focus on benchmarking and evaluation (cs.SY). Finally, the use of robotic environments suggests a possible focus on computer vision (cs.CV) for perception tasks.
